Package: fdaMixedRTMB
Type: Package
Title: Operator-Based Functional Mixed Models with Boundary-Value Estimation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mille", "Thostrup", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "mrt@math.ku.dk")
  )
Author: Mille Thostrup [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Mille Thostrup <mrt@math.ku.dk>
Description: Operator-based functional mixed models fit via the Markussen
    (2013) operator-projection / trace-integral REML approximation differentiated
    by RTMB. Supports K.order = 1 operators from fdaMixed: L f = -lambda_d2 f''
    (pure Laplace) and L f = -lambda_d2 f'' + lambda_level f (shifted Laplace).
    The main interface is fdaLm_rtmb(), which mirrors fdaMixed::fdaLm() and
    accepts formulas for the fixed, random, and boundary-value regressions. The
    user supplies left and right boundary operators; curve-specific right
    boundary values are estimated through a null-space carrier h(t), which
    enters as ordinary fixed-effect columns that are profiled out analytically.
    sigma^2 and all fixed effects are eliminated from the REML objective via
    forward-backward Green's-function projection sweeps; the REML log-determinant
    trace contribution is approximated by fixed Gauss-Legendre quadrature of the
    Markussen trace integral; grouped random effects are optionally marginalized
    by an RTMB Laplace approximation; and nlminb() optimizes the outer variance
    parameters using RTMB automatic differentiation. No latent serial-coefficient
    block is introduced.
